        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-08T19:20:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well I know in Vulkan the command buffer can finish and we notice it inside of the onFinishFlush call. So it would be nice for that to work easily. I think (though we should check) the completion callbacks in metal are asynchronous and could be triggered at any time.\n\nSo yeah if we keep the current model I think we will need a function call to move all active to busy.",
